        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  ages between 18 and 65 years

          -  a diagnosis of low back pain with onset > 12 weeks based on the evaluation by
             physician

          -  average pain intensity score of â¥ 3 on NPRS.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  they have acute disc prolapse or protusion with neurological sign and symptoms in the
             past 3-months;

          -  bacterial spondylitis;

          -  Rheumatoid arthritis;

          -  ankylosing spondylitis;

          -  back pain secondary to bone malignancy

          -  spinal fracture;

          -  osteoporotic collapse;

          -  cauda equina compression

          -  prior spinal surgery;

          -  psychiatric disorder (e.g. psychosis / delusion);

          -  current pregnancy

          -  previous experience with Bowen therapy.
